This provides static methods to convert comma delimited text into a JSONArray and to covert a JSONArray into comma delimited text Comma delimited text is a very popular format for data interchange It is understood by most database spreadsheet and organizer programs p Each row of text represents a row in a table or a data record Each row ends with a NEWLINE character Each row contains one or more values Values are separated by commas A value can contain any character except for comma unless is is wrapped in single quotes or double quotes p The first row usually contains the names of the columns p A comma delimited list can be converted into a JSONArray of JSONObjects The names for the elements in the JSONObjects can be taken from the names in the first row author JSON org version;
